
Visual nonlinearities and perceived "shimmer"

Over fifty years ago, MacKay reported on effects of viewing a pattern
of finely-spaced black and white radial sectors.  While he was primarily
concerned with the afteraffects resulting from viewing these patterns,
he also noted certain effects that occurred during direct viewing.
Similar effects have been noted with regard to other images containing
finely spaced lines, in particular the op-art painting "Fall" by Bridget
Riley.  Various explanations have been proposed, including
